To utilize a QueryExpander, you would implement the interface with your specific expansion logic. For example:

Query originalQuery = new Query("fuzzy search term");
QueryExpander myExpander = new MyCustomQueryExpander(); // An implementation of QueryExpander
List<Query> expandedQueries = myExpander.expand(originalQuery);
// expandedQueries might contain ["fuzzy search term corrected", "exact search term", "related search term"]

Due to extending `Function`, it can also be used functionally:
Function<Query, List<Query>> queryExpansionFunction = new MyCustomQueryExpander();
List<Query> results = queryExpansionFunction.apply(new Query("complex request"));
